#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:4.1"
msgid "Dutiya­pā­rāji­ka­sikkhā­pada"
msgstr "2. The second training rule"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:5.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:5.2"
msgid ""
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="Bu-Pj.2"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="Bu-Pj.2.1"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.2.1.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.64"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.41"></a> <a class="ms-pa" id="ms.191"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:5.3"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā rājagahe viharati gijjhakūṭe pabbate."
msgstr "At one time, the Buddha was staying at Rājagaha on Mount Vulture Peak."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:5.4"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā sandiṭṭhā sambhattā bhikkhū isigilipasse tiṇakuṭiyo karitvā vassaṃ upagacchiṃsu."
msgstr "At that time a number of monks who were friends had made grass huts on the slope of Mount Isigili and had entered the rains there."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:5.5"
msgid "Āyasmāpi dhaniyo kumbha­kā­ra­putto tiṇakuṭikaṃ karitvā vassaṃ upagacchi."
msgstr "Among them was Venerable Dhaniya, the potter’s son."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:5.6"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū vassaṃvuṭṭhā temāsaccayena tiṇakuṭiyo bhinditvā tiṇañca kaṭṭhañca paṭisāmetvā jana­pada­cārikaṃ pakkamiṃsu."
msgstr "After three months, when the rains residence was over, the monks demolished their grass huts, put away the grass and wood, and departed to wander around the country."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:5.7"
msgid "Āyasmā pana dhaniyo kumbha­kā­ra­putto tattheva vassaṃ vasi, tattha hemantaṃ, tattha gimhaṃ."
msgstr "But Venerable Dhaniya also spent the winter and the summer there."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:5.8"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato dhaniyassa kumbha­kā­ra­puttassa gāmaṃ piṇḍāya paviṭṭhassa tiṇahāriyo kaṭṭhahāriyo tiṇakuṭikaṃ bhinditvā tiṇañca kaṭṭhañca ādāya agamaṃsu."
msgstr "Then, on one occasion, while Venerable Dhaniya was in the village to collect almsfood, some women gathering grass and firewood demolished the grass hut and took away the grass and sticks."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:5.9"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho āyasmā dhaniyo kumbha­kā­ra­putto tiṇañca kaṭṭhañca saṅkaḍḍhitvā tiṇakuṭikaṃ akāsi."
msgstr "A second time Dhaniya collected grass and sticks and made a grass hut,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:5.10"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho āyasmato dhaniyassa kumbha­kā­ra­puttassa gāmaṃ piṇḍāya paviṭṭhassa tiṇahāriyo kaṭṭhahāriyo tiṇakuṭikaṃ bhinditvā tiṇañca kaṭṭhañca ādāya agamaṃsu."
msgstr "and again the hut was demolished in the same way."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:5.11"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho āyasmā dhaniyo kumbha­kā­ra­putto tiṇañca kaṭṭhañca saṅkaḍḍhitvā tiṇakuṭikaṃ akāsi."
msgstr "The same thing happened a third time."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:5.12"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho āyasmato dhaniyassa kumbha­kā­ra­puttassa gāmaṃ piṇḍāya paviṭṭhassa tiṇahāriyo kaṭṭhahāriyo tiṇakuṭikaṃ bhinditvā tiṇañca kaṭṭhañca ādāya agamaṃsu."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.192"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.65"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:6.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato dhaniyassa kumbha­kā­ra­puttassa etadahosi—"
msgstr "Dhaniya thought,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:6.2"
msgid "“yāvatatiyakaṃ kho me gāmaṃ piṇḍāya paviṭṭhassa tiṇahāriyo kaṭṭhahāriyo tiṇakuṭikaṃ bhinditvā tiṇañca kaṭṭhañca ādāya agamaṃsu."
msgstr "“Three times this has happened."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:6.3"
msgid "Ahaṃ kho pana susikkhito anavayo sake ācariyake kumbha­kā­ra­kamme pari­yodāta­sippo."
msgstr "But I’m well-trained and experienced in my own craft of pottery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:6.4"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ sāmaṃ cikkhallaṃ madditvā sab­bamat­tikā­mayaṃ kuṭikaṃ kareyyan”ti."
msgstr "Why don’t I knead mud myself and make a hut consisting of nothing but clay?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.193"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.42"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:7.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā dhaniyo kumbha­kā­ra­putto sāmaṃ cikkhallaṃ madditvā sab­bamat­tikā­mayaṃ kuṭikaṃ karitvā tiṇañca kaṭṭhañca gomayañca saṅkaḍḍhitvā taṃ kuṭikaṃ paci."
msgstr "Then Dhaniya did just that. And he collected grass, wood, and cow-dung, and he baked his hut."

#. VAR: lohitikā → lohitakā (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:7.2"
msgid "Sā ahosi kuṭikā abhirūpā dassanīyā pāsādikā lohitikā, seyyathāpi indagopako."
msgstr "It was a beautiful and charming little hut, and it was red just like a scarlet rain-mite."

#. VAR: kiṅkaṇikasaddo → kiṅkiṇikasaddo (bj, s1-3) | kiṅkiṇikāsaddo (pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:7.3"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma kiṅkaṇikasaddo; evamevaṃ tassā kuṭikāya saddo ahosi."
msgstr "And when hit it sounded just like the sound of a bell."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.2.1.2"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.194"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:8.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā sambahulehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohanto addasa taṃ kuṭikaṃ abhirūpaṃ dassanīyaṃ pāsādikaṃ lohitikaṃ."
msgstr "Just then the Master, while descending from Mount Vulture Peak with a number of monks, saw that hut."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:8.2"
msgid "Disvāna bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "He said to the monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:8.3"
msgid "“kiṃ etaṃ, bhikkhave, abhirūpaṃ dassanīyaṃ pāsādikaṃ lohitikaṃ, seyyathāpi indagopako”ti?"
msgstr "“Monks, what’s this beautiful and charming thing, which is red like a scarlet rain-mite?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:8.4"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "The monks informed the Master,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:8.5"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā—"
msgstr "and the Buddha criticized Dhaniya:"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:8.6"
msgid "“ananucchavikaṃ, bhikkhave, tassa moghapurisassa ananulomikaṃ appatirūpaṃ assāmaṇakaṃ akappiyaṃ akaraṇīyaṃ."
msgstr "“It’s not suitable, monks, for that foolish man, it’s not proper, it’s not worthy of an ascetic, it’s not allowable, it’s not to be done."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:8.7"
msgid "Kathañhi nāma so, bhikkhave, moghapuriso sab­bamat­tikā­mayaṃ kuṭikaṃ karissati."
msgstr "How can he make a hut out of nothing but clay?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:8.8"
msgid "Na hi nāma, bhikkhave, tassa moghapurisassa pāṇesu anuddayā anukampā avihesā bhavissati."
msgstr "Certainly that foolish man can have no consideration, compassion, and mercy for living beings."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.66"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:8.9"
msgid "Gacchathetaṃ, bhikkhave, kuṭikaṃ bhindatha."
msgstr "Go, monks, and demolish this hut."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:8.10"
msgid "Mā pacchimā janatā pāṇesu pātabyataṃ āpajji."
msgstr "Don’t let future generations take up the destruction of living beings."

#. <strong class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:8.11"
msgid "Na ca, bhikkhave, sab­bamat­tikā­mayā kuṭikā kātabbā."
msgstr "And, monks, you should not make a hut consisting of nothing but clay."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:8.12"
msgid "Yo kareyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti."
msgstr "If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”"

#. </strong></p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.67"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:8.13"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti, kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paṭissuṇitvā yena sā kuṭikā tenu­pasaṅka­miṃsu;"
msgstr "“Yes, Venerable,” the monks replied, and they went to that hut"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:8.14"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā taṃ kuṭikaṃ bhindiṃsu."
msgstr "an demolished it."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:8.15"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā dhaniyo kumbha­kā­ra­putto te bhikkhū etadavoca—"
msgstr "Dhaniya said to them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:8.16"
msgid "“kissa me tumhe, āvuso, kuṭikaṃ bhindathā”ti?"
msgstr "“Why are you demolishing my hut?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:8.17"
msgid "“Bhagavā, āvuso, bhedāpetī”ti."
msgstr "“The Master has asked us to.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:8.18"
msgid "“Bhindathāvuso, sace dhammassāmī bhedāpetī”ti."
msgstr "“Demolish it, if the Lord of the Truth has said so.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.2.1.3"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.195"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:9.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato dhaniyassa kumbha­kā­ra­puttassa etadahosi—"
msgstr "Then Dhaniya thought,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:9.2"
msgid "“yāvatatiyakaṃ kho me gāmaṃ piṇḍāya paviṭṭhassa tiṇahāriyo kaṭṭhahāriyo tiṇakuṭikaṃ bhinditvā tiṇañca kaṭṭhañca ādāya agamaṃsu."
msgstr "“Three times, while I was in the village to collect almsfood, women gathering grass and firewood demolished my hut and took away the grass and sticks."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:9.3"
msgid "Yāpi mayā sab­bamat­tikā­mayā kuṭikā katā sāpi bhagavatā bhedāpitā."
msgstr "And now my hut made of nothing but clay has been demolished at the Master’s request."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:9.4"
msgid "Atthi ca me dārugahe gaṇako sandiṭṭho."
msgstr "But the caretaker of the wood-store is a friend of mine."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:9.5"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ dārugahe gaṇakaṃ dārūni yācitvā dārukuṭikaṃ kareyyan”ti."
msgstr "Why don’t I ask him for wood and make a hut out of that?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.196"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:10.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā dhaniyo kumbha­kā­ra­putto yena dārugahe gaṇako tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Dhaniya then went to the caretaker of the wood-store"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:10.2"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā dārugahe gaṇakaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and told him what had happened, adding:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:10.3"
msgid "“yāvatatiyakaṃ kho me, āvuso, gāmaṃ piṇḍāya paviṭṭhassa tiṇahāriyo kaṭṭhahāriyo tiṇakuṭikaṃ bhinditvā tiṇañca kaṭṭhañca ādāya agamaṃsu."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:10.4"
msgid "Yāpi mayā sab­bamat­tikā­mayā kuṭikā katā sāpi bhagavatā bhedāpitā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:10.5"
msgid "Dehi me, āvuso, dārūni."
msgstr "“Please give me some wood,"

#. VAR: dārukuṭikaṃ → dārukuḍḍikaṃ kuṭikaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:10.6"
msgid "Icchāmi dārukuṭikaṃ kātun”ti."
msgstr "I want to make a wooden hut.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:10.7"
msgid "“Natthi, bhante, tādisāni dārūni yānāhaṃ ayyassa dadeyyaṃ."
msgstr "“There’s no such wood, Venerable, that I could give you."

#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.43"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:10.8"
msgid "Atthi, bhante, devagahadārūni nagara­paṭi­saṅ­khā­ri­kāni āpadatthāya nikkhittāni."
msgstr "This wood is held by the King, and it’s meant for the repair of the town and put aside in case of emergencies."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:10.9"
msgid "Sace tāni dārūni rājā dāpeti harāpetha, bhante”ti."
msgstr "You can only take it if the King gives it away.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:10.10"
msgid "“Dinnāni, āvuso, raññā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s been given by the King.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.197"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:11.1"
msgid "Atha kho dārugahe gaṇakassa etadahosi—"
msgstr "The caretaker of the wood-store thought,"

#. VAR: samacārino → sammacārino (mr)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:11.2"
msgid "“ime kho samaṇā sakyaputtiyā dhammacārino samacārino brahmacārino saccavādino sīlavanto kalyāṇadhammā."
msgstr "“These Sakyan ascetics live according to the Truth. They are celibate and their conduct is good, and they are truthful, moral, and have a good character."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:11.3"
msgid "Rājāpimesaṃ abhippasanno."
msgstr "Even the King has faith in them."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:11.4"
msgid "Nārahati adinnaṃ dinnanti vattun”ti."
msgstr "These venerables wouldn’t say something is given if it were not.”"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.68"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:11.5"
msgid "Atha kho dārugahe gaṇako āyasmantaṃ dhaniyaṃ kumbha­kā­ra­puttaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "And he said to Dhaniya,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:11.6"
msgid "“harāpetha, bhante”ti."
msgstr "“You may take it, Venerable.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:11.7"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā dhaniyo kumbha­kā­ra­putto tāni dārūni khaṇ­ḍā­khaṇ­ḍikaṃ chedāpetvā sakaṭehi nibbāhāpetvā dārukuṭikaṃ akāsi."
msgstr "Dhaniya then had that wood broken up into pieces, removed it by means of carts, and made a wooden hut."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.2.1.4"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.198"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:12.1"
msgid "Atha kho vassakāro brāhmaṇo maga­dha­mahā­matto rājagahe kammante anusaññāyamāno yena dārugahe gaṇako tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Soon afterwards the brahmin Vassakāra, the chief minister of Magadha, while inspecting the works in Rājagaha, went to the caretaker of the wood-store"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:12.2"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā dārugahe gaṇakaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said to him:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:12.3"
msgid "“yāni tāni, bhaṇe,"
msgstr "“What’s going on?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:12.4"
msgid "devagahadārūni nagara­paṭi­saṅ­khā­ri­kāni āpadatthāya nikkhittāni kahaṃ tāni dārūnī”ti?"
msgstr "Where’s the wood held by the King that’s meant for the repair of the town and put aside in case of emergencies?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:12.5"
msgid "“Tāni, sāmi, dārūni devena ayyassa dhaniyassa kumbha­kā­ra­puttassa dinnānī”ti."
msgstr "“Sir, that wood was given by the King to Venerable Dhaniya.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.199"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:13.1"
msgid "Atha kho vassakāro brāhmaṇo maga­dha­mahā­matto anattamano ahosi—"
msgstr "The brahmin Vassakāra was upset and thought,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:13.2"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma devo devagahadārūni nagara­paṭi­saṅ­khā­ri­kāni āpadatthāya nikkhittāni dhaniyassa kumbha­kā­ra­puttassa dassatī”ti."
msgstr "“How could the King give away this wood to Dhaniya, the potter’s son?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:13.3"
msgid "Atha kho vassakāro brāhmaṇo maga­dha­mahā­matto yena rājā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "The brahmin Vassakāra then went to King Seniya Bimbisāra of Magadha"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:13.4"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā rājānaṃ māgadhaṃ seniyaṃ bimbisāraṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said,"

#. VAR: saccaṃ kira devena → saccaṃ kira deva devena (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:13.5"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira devena devagahadārūni nagara­paṭi­saṅ­khā­ri­kāni āpadatthāya nikkhittāni dhaniyassa kumbha­kā­ra­puttassa dinnānī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, sir, that the wood held by the King, meant for the repair of the town and put aside in case of emergencies was given by the King to Dhaniya, the potter’s son?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:13.6"
msgid "“Ko evamāhā”ti?"
msgstr "“Who said that?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:13.7"
msgid "“Dārugahe gaṇako, devā”ti."
msgstr "“The caretaker of the wood-store, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:13.8"
msgid "“Tena hi, brāhmaṇa, dārugahe gaṇakaṃ āṇāpehī”ti."
msgstr "“Well then, brahmin, send for the caretaker of the wood-store.”"

#. VAR: bandhaṃ → baddhaṃ (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:13.9"
msgid "Atha kho vassakāro brāhmaṇo maga­dha­mahā­matto dārugahe gaṇakaṃ bandhaṃ āṇāpesi."
msgstr "And Vassakāra had the caretaker of the wood-store bound and taken by force."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.200"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.69"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:14.1"
msgid "Addasa kho āyasmā dhaniyo kumbha­kā­ra­putto dārugahe gaṇakaṃ bandhaṃ niyyamānaṃ."
msgstr "Dhaniya saw the caretaker of the wood-store being bound and taken by force,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:14.2"
msgid "Disvāna dārugahe gaṇakaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and he said to him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:14.3"
msgid "“kissa tvaṃ, āvuso, bandho niyyāsī”ti?"
msgstr "“Why is this happening to you?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:14.4"
msgid "“Tesaṃ, bhante, dārūnaṃ kiccā”ti."
msgstr "“Because of that business with the wood, Venerable.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:14.5"
msgid "“Gacchāvuso, ahampi āgacchāmī”ti."
msgstr "“Go, and I’ll come too.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:14.6"
msgid "“Eyyāsi, bhante, purāhaṃ haññāmī”ti."
msgstr "“Please come before I’m done for.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.2.1.5"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.201"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:15.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā dhaniyo kumbha­kā­ra­putto yena rañño māgadhassa seniyassa bimbisārassa nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Dhaniya then went to the dwelling of King Bimbisāra"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:15.2"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi."
msgstr " and sat down on the appointed seat."

#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.44"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:15.3"
msgid "Atha kho rājā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro yenāyasmā dhaniyo kumbha­kā­ra­putto tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "The King approached Dhaniya,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:15.4"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ dhaniyaṃ kumbha­kā­ra­puttaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "bowed down to him, and sat down to one side."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:15.5"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho rājā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro āyasmantaṃ dhaniyaṃ kumbha­kā­ra­puttaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "He then said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:15.6"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira mayā, bhante, devagahadārūni nagara­paṭi­saṅ­khā­ri­kāni āpadatthāya nikkhittāni ayyassa dinnānī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, Venerable, that I have given the wood held by the King—meant for the repair of the town and put aside in case of emergencies—to you?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:15.7"
msgid "“Evaṃ, mahārājā”ti."
msgstr "“Yes, great king.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:15.8"
msgid "“Mayaṃ kho, bhante, rājāno nāma bahukiccā bahukaraṇīyā,"
msgstr "“We kings are very busy—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:15.9"
msgid "datvāpi na sareyyāma;"
msgstr "we may give and not remember."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:15.10"
msgid "iṅgha, bhante, sarāpehī”ti."
msgstr "Please remind me, Venerable.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:15.11"
msgid "“Sarasi tvaṃ, mahārāja, paṭha­mā­bhisitto evarūpiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā—"
msgstr "“Do you remember, great king, when you were first anointed, speaking these words:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:15.12"
msgid "‘dinnaññeva samaṇab­rāhma­ṇā­naṃ tiṇakaṭ­ṭho­dakaṃ paribhuñjantū’”ti."
msgstr "‘Let the ascetics and brahmins enjoy gifts of grass, sticks, and water’?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:15.13"
msgid "“Sarāmahaṃ, bhante."
msgstr "“I remember, Venerable."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:15.14"
msgid "Santi, bhante, samaṇabrāhmaṇā lajjino kukkuccakā sikkhākāmā."
msgstr "There are ascetics and brahmins who have a sense of conscience, who are afraid of wrongdoing and desirous of training."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:15.15"
msgid "Tesaṃ appamattakepi kukkuccaṃ uppajjati."
msgstr "They have a sense of conscience even in regard to small matters."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:15.16"
msgid "Tesaṃ mayā sandhāya bhāsitaṃ, tañca kho araññe apariggahitaṃ."
msgstr "What was uttered by me was meant for these, and it concerned what’s ownerless in the wilderness."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:15.17"
msgid "So tvaṃ, bhante, tena lesena dārūni adinnaṃ harituṃ maññasi."
msgstr "Yet you, Venerable, imagine that you can take wood not given to you by means of this trick?"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.70"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:15.18"
msgid "Kathañhi nāma mādiso samaṇaṃ vā brāhmaṇaṃ vā vijite vasantaṃ haneyya vā bandheyya vā pabbājeyya vā."
msgstr "But how could I presume to beat, imprison, or banish an ascetic or a brahmin living in my kingdom?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:15.19"
msgid "Gaccha, bhante, lomena tvaṃ muttosi."
msgstr "Go, you’re free because of your status,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:15.20"
msgid "Māssu punapi evarūpaṃ akāsī”ti."
msgstr "but don’t do such a thing again.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.2.1.6"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.202"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:16.1"
msgid "Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "But people grumbled and complained:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:16.2"
msgid "“alajjino ime samaṇā sakyaputtiyā dussīlā musāvādino."
msgstr "“These Sakyan ascetics are shameless and immoral liars."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:16.3"
msgid "Ime hi nāma dhammacārino samacārino brāhmacārino saccavādino sīlavanto kalyāṇadhammā paṭijānissanti."
msgstr "They claim to live according to the Truth, to be celibate and of good conduct, to be truthful, moral, and of good character."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:16.4"
msgid "Natthi imesaṃ sāmaññaṃ, natthi imesaṃ brahmaññaṃ."
msgstr "But they don’t have the qualities of an ascetic or a brahmin;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:16.5"
msgid "Naṭṭhaṃ imesaṃ sāmaññaṃ, naṭṭhaṃ imesaṃ brahmaññaṃ."
msgstr "they’ve lost the plot."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:16.6"
msgid "Kuto imesaṃ sāmaññaṃ, kuto imesaṃ brahmaññaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:16.7"
msgid "Apagatā ime sāmaññā, apagatā ime brahmaññā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:16.8"
msgid "Rājānampi ime vañcenti, kiṃ panaññe manusse”ti."
msgstr "They even deceive the King—what then other people?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.203"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:17.1"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ."
msgstr "Monks heard the complaints of those people."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:17.2"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā santuṭṭhā lajjino kukkuccakā sikkhākāmā te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "The monks of few desires who had a sense of conscience, who were contented, afraid of wrongdoing, and desirous of training, complained and criticized Venerable Dhaniya:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:17.3"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma āyasmā dhaniyo kumbha­kā­ra­putto rañño dārūni adinnaṃ ādiyissatī”ti."
msgstr "“How can he take wood belonging to the King that hasn’t been given to him?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.204"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:18.1"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ dhaniyaṃ kumbha­kā­ra­puttaṃ aneka­pariyā­yena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "After criticizing Dhaniya in many ways, they informed the Master."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:18.2"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṃghaṃ sannipātāpetvā āyasmantaṃ dhaniyaṃ kumbha­kā­ra­puttaṃ paṭipucchi—"
msgstr "The Master then convened the Order of monks and questioned Venerable Dhaniya:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:18.3"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, dhaniya, rañño dārūni adinnaṃ ādiyī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, Dhaniya, that you’ve taken wood belonging to the King that wasn’t given to you?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:18.4"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.71"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:18.5"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā—"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:18.6"
msgid "“ananucchavikaṃ, moghapurisa, ananulomikaṃ appatirūpaṃ assāmaṇakaṃ akappiyaṃ akaraṇīyaṃ."
msgstr "“Foolish man, it’s not suitable, it’s not proper, it’s not worthy of an ascetic, it’s not allowable, it’s not to be done."

#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.45"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:18.7"
msgid "Kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, rañño dārūni adinnaṃ ādiyissasi."
msgstr "How can you take wood belonging to the King that hasn’t been given to you?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:18.8"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya pasannānaṃ vā bhiyyobhāvāya;"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it or increase the confidence of those who have it,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:18.9"
msgid "atha khvetaṃ, moghapurisa, appasan­nā­nañ­ceva appasādāya pasannānañca ekaccānaṃ aññathattāyā”ti."
msgstr "but it will hinder confidence in those without it, and it will cause some with confidence to change their minds.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.205"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:19.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññataro purāṇavohāriko mahāmatto bhikkhūsu pabbajito bhagavato avidūre nisinno hoti."
msgstr "At that time a former judge who had gone forth with the monks was sitting near the Master."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:19.2"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "The Master said to him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:19.3"
msgid "“kittakena kho, bhikkhu, rājā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro coraṃ gahetvā hanati vā bandhati vā pabbājeti vā”ti?"
msgstr "“For what amount of theft does King Bimbisāra beat, imprison, or banish a thief?”"

#. </p><p>
#. VAR: Pādena vā, bhagavā, pādārahena vā”ti → pādārahena vā atirekapādena vāti (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:19.4"
msgid "“Pādena vā, bhagavā, pādārahena vā”ti."
msgstr "“For a <i lang=\"pli\">pāda</i> coin, Master, for the worth of a <i lang=\"pli\">pāda</i>, or for more than a <i lang=\"pli\">pāda</i>.”"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.72"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:19.5"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena rājagahe pañcamāsako pādo hoti."
msgstr "At that time in Rājagaha a <i lang=\"pli\">pāda</i> coin was worth five <i lang=\"pli\">māsaka</i> coins."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:19.6"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ dhaniyaṃ kumbha­kā­ra­puttaṃ aneka­pariyā­yena vigarahitvā dubbharatāya … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing Venerable Dhaniya in many ways for being difficult to support … “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:19.7"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:20.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Preliminary ruling"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.206"></a>
#. <strong class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:20.2"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu adinnaṃ they­ya­saṅ­khā­taṃ ādiyeyya,"
msgstr "‘If a monk, intending to steal, takes what has not been given to him—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:20.3"
msgid "yathārūpe adinnādāne rājāno coraṃ gahetvā haneyyuṃ vā bandheyyuṃ vā pabbājeyyuṃ vā—"
msgstr "the sort of theft for which kings, having caught a thief, would beat, imprison, or banish him, saying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:20.4"
msgid "‘corosi bālosi mūḷhosi thenosī’ti,"
msgstr "“You’re a bandit, you’re a fool, you’ve gone astray, you’re a thief”—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:20.5"
msgid "tathārūpaṃ bhikkhu adinnaṃ ādiyamāno ayampi pārājiko hoti asaṃvāso”ti."
msgstr "he too is expelled and not in communion.’”"

#. </strong>
#. </p><p class="endsection"><a class="sc" id="17"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.207"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:21.1"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:22.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.2.2"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.208"></a>
#. <span class="note" hidden>The text simply says “the dyers’ spread,” <i lang="pli">rajakattharaṇaṃ</i>, but the commentary qualifies that this refers to their spread of “cloth,” <i lang="pli">vatthāni</i>, see <span class="ref">Sp.2.298.17</span>.</span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:22.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū raja­kattha­ra­ṇaṃ gantvā rajaka­bhaṇḍi­kaṃ avaharitvā ārāmaṃ haritvā bhājesuṃ."
msgstr "At one time monks from the group of six went to the dyers’ spread of cloth, took the dyers’ goods to the monastery, and shared it out."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:22.3"
msgid "Bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "Other monks said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:22.4"
msgid "“mahāpuññattha tumhe, āvuso."
msgstr "“You have great merit,"

#. <span class="note" hidden>In addition to meaning a finished robe, according to the definition of <i lang="pli">cīvara</i> at <i lang="pli">nissaggiya pācittiya</i> 1 <span class="ref">MS.1.1872</span>, it also refers to pieces of robe-cloth. This means that I vary my translation depending on the context. Sometimes, such as here, the meaning seems to encompass both robes and robe-cloth, and I then render it as robe(-cloth).</span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:22.5"
msgid "Bahuṃ tumhākaṃ cīvaraṃ uppannan”ti."
msgstr "since you’ve obtained so much robe(-cloth).”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:22.6"
msgid "“Kuto, āvuso, amhākaṃ puññaṃ,"
msgstr "“How is there merit for us?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:22.7"
msgid "idāni mayaṃ raja­kattha­ra­ṇaṃ gantvā rajaka­bhaṇḍi­kaṃ avaharimhā”ti."
msgstr "Just now we went to the dyers’ spread of cloth and took the dyers’ goods.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:22.8"
msgid "“Nanu, āvuso, bhagavatā sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ."
msgstr "“Hasn’t a training rule been laid down by the Master?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:22.9"
msgid "Kissa tumhe, āvuso, rajaka­bhaṇḍi­kaṃ avaharitthā”ti?"
msgstr "Why then do you take the dyers’ goods?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:22.10"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ."
msgstr "“It’s true that a training rule has been laid down by the Master,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:22.11"
msgid "Tañca kho gāme, no araññe”ti."
msgstr "but it concerns the village, not the wilderness.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:22.12"
msgid "“Nanu, āvuso, tathevetaṃ hoti."
msgstr "“But that’s just the same."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.73"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:22.13"
msgid "Ananucchavikaṃ, āvuso, ananulomikaṃ appatirūpaṃ assāmaṇakaṃ akappiyaṃ akaraṇīyaṃ."
msgstr "It’s not suitable, it’s not proper, it’s not worthy of an ascetic, it’s not allowable, it’s not to be done."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:22.14"
msgid "Kathañhi nāma tumhe, āvuso, rajaka­bhaṇḍi­kaṃ avaharissatha."
msgstr "How can you take the dyers’s goods?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:22.15"
msgid "Netaṃ, āvuso, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya pasannānaṃ vā bhiyyobhāvāya;"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it or increase the confidence of those who have it,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:22.16"
msgid "atha khvetaṃ, āvuso, appasan­nā­nañ­ceva appasādāya pasannānañca ekaccānaṃ aññathattāyā”ti."
msgstr "but it will hinder confidence in those without it and it will cause some with confidence to change their minds.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.46"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:22.17"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū chabbaggiye bhikkhū aneka­pariyā­yena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "After criticizing those monks in various ways, they informed the Master."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="19"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.209"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:23.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṃghaṃ sannipātāpetvā chabbaggiye bhikkhū paṭipucchi—"
msgstr "The Master convened the Order of monks and questioned those monks:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:23.2"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, raja­kattha­ra­ṇaṃ gantvā rajaka­bhaṇḍi­kaṃ avaharitthā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you went to the dyers’ spread of cloth and took the dyers’ goods?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:23.3"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:23.4"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā—"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:23.5"
msgid "“ananucchavikaṃ, moghapurisā, ananulomikaṃ appaṭirūpaṃ assāmaṇakaṃ akappiyaṃ akaraṇīyaṃ."
msgstr "“It’s not suitable, foolish men, it’s not proper, it’s not worthy of an ascetic, it’s not allowable, it’s not to be done."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:23.6"
msgid "Kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, rajaka­bhaṇḍi­kaṃ avaharissatha."
msgstr "How can you go to the dyers’ spread of cloth and take the dyers’ goods?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:23.7"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya pasannānaṃ vā bhiyyobhāvāya;"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it or increase the confidence of those who have it,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:23.8"
msgid "atha khvetaṃ, moghapurisā, appasan­nā­nañ­ceva appasādāya pasannānañca ekaccānaṃ aññathattāyā”ti."
msgstr "but it will hinder confidence in those without it, and it will cause some with confidence to change their minds.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:23.9"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā chabbaggiye bhikkhū aneka­pariyā­yena vigarahitvā dubbharatāya … pe …"
msgstr "Then, after criticizing those monks from the group of six in various ways, the Master spoke in dispraise of being difficult to support …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:23.10"
msgid "vīriyā­rambhassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsitvā bhikkhūnaṃ tadanuc­chavi­kaṃ tadanulomikaṃ dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi … pe"
msgstr "but he spoke in praise … of putting forth energy. Having given a teaching on what is right and proper, he addressed the monks …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:23.11"
msgid "… evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "“… And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:24.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="20"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.210"></a>
#. <strong class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:24.2"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu gāmā vā araññā vā adinnaṃ they­ya­saṅ­khā­taṃ ādiyeyya,"
msgstr "‘If a monk, intending to steal, takes from a village or from the wilderness what has not been given to him—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:24.3"
msgid "yathārūpe adinnādāne rājāno coraṃ gahetvā haneyyuṃ vā bandheyyuṃ vā pabbājeyyuṃ vā—"
msgstr "the sort of theft for which kings, having caught a thief, would beat, imprison, or banish him, saying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:24.4"
msgid "‘corosi bālosi mūḷhosi thenosī’ti, tathārūpaṃ bhikkhu adinnaṃ ādiyamāno ayampi pārājiko hoti asaṃvāso”ti."
msgstr "“You’re a bandit, you’re a fool, you’ve gone astray, you’re a thief”—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:24.5"
msgid "tathārūpaṃ bhikkhu adinnaṃ ādiyamāno ayampi pārājiko hoti asaṃvāso”ti."
msgstr "he too is expelled and not in communion.’”"

#. </strong> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:24.6"
msgid "(<em>2</em>:<strong>2</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:25.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="21"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.2.3"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.211"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:25.2"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. </strong>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:25.3"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. </span>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:25.4"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:25.5"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr "… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a formal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:25.6"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="22"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.74"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.212"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:26.1"
msgid "Gāmo nāma"
msgstr "A village:"

#. </strong>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:26.2"
msgid "ekakuṭikopi gāmo, dvikuṭikopi gāmo, tikuṭikopi gāmo, catukuṭikopi gāmo, samanussopi gāmo, amanussopi gāmo, parikkhittopi gāmo, aparikkhittopi gāmo, gonisādi­niviṭṭhopi gāmo, yopi sattho ati­reka­catumā­sani­viṭṭho sopi vuccati gāmo."
msgstr "a village of one hut, a village of two huts, a village of three huts, a village of four huts, an inhabited village, an uninhabited village, an enclosed village, an unenclosed village, a disorganized village, and even a caravan settled for more than four months is called “a village.”"

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="23"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:27.1"
msgid "Gāmūpacāro nāma"
msgstr "The vicinity of a village:"

#. </strong>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
#. VAR: indakhīle → indakhile (mr)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:27.2"
msgid "parikkhittassa gāmassa indakhīle ṭhitassa majjhimassa purisassa leḍḍupāto,"
msgstr "of an enclosed village: the outward stone-throw of a man of average height standing at the threshold of the village gateway;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:27.3"
msgid "aparik­khit­tassa gāmassa gharūpacāre ṭhitassa majjhimassa purisassa leḍḍupāto."
msgstr "of an unenclosed village: the outward stone-throw of a man of average height standing within the vicinity of a house."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="24"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.214"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:28.1"
msgid "Araññaṃ nāma"
msgstr "The wilderness:"

#. </strong>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:28.2"
msgid "ṭhapetvā gāmañca gāmūpacārañca avasesaṃ araññaṃ nāma."
msgstr "apart from the village and the vicinity of the village, the remainder is called “the wilderness.”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="25"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.215"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:29.1"
msgid "Adinnaṃ nāma"
msgstr "What has not been given:"

#. </strong>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:29.2"
msgid "yaṃ adinnaṃ anissaṭṭhaṃ apariccattaṃ rakkhitaṃ gopitaṃ mamāyitaṃ paraparig­gahi­taṃ."
msgstr "what has not been given, what has not been let go of, what has not been relinquished; what is guarded, what is protected, what is regarded as “mine”;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:29.3"
msgid "paraparig­gahi­taṃ."
msgstr "what belongs to someone else."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:29.4"
msgid "Etaṃ adinnaṃ nāma."
msgstr "This is called “what has not been given.”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="26"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.216"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:30.1"
msgid "They­ya­saṅ­khā­tanti"
msgstr "Intending to steal:"

#. </strong>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:30.2"
msgid "theyyacitto avaharaṇacitto."
msgstr "the thought of stealing, the thought of taking."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="27"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.217"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:31.1"
msgid "Ādiyeyyāti"
msgstr "Takes:"

#. </strong>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:31.2"
msgid "ādiyeyya hareyya avahareyya iriyāpathaṃ vikopeyya ṭhānā cāveyya saṅketaṃ vītināmeyya."
msgstr "takes, carries off, takes away, interrupts the movement of, removes from its base, does not fulfill an agreement."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="28"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.218"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:32.1"
msgid "Yathārūpaṃ nāma"
msgstr "The sort:"

#. </strong>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:32.2"
msgid "pādaṃ vā pādārahaṃ vā atirekapādaṃ vā."
msgstr "a <i lang=\"pli\">pāda</i> coin, the worth of a <i lang=\"pli\">pāda</i>, or more than a <i lang=\"pli\">pāda</i>."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="29"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.47"></a> <a class="ms-pa" id="ms.219"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:33.1"
msgid "Rājāno nāma"
msgstr "Kings:"

#. </strong>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:33.2"
msgid "pathabyārājā padesarājā maṇḍalikā antarabhogikā akkhadassā mahāmattā, ye vā pana chejjabhejjaṃ karontā anusāsanti."
msgstr "kings of the earth, kings of a region, rulers of islands, rulers of border areas, judges, ministers, or whoever metes out physical punishment—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:33.3"
msgid "Ete rājāno nāma."
msgstr "these are called “kings.”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="30"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.75"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.220"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:34.1"
msgid "Coro nāma"
msgstr "A thief:"

#. </strong>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:34.2"
msgid "yo pañcamāsakaṃ vā ati­reka­pañca­māsakaṃ vā agghanakaṃ adinnaṃ they­ya­saṅ­khā­taṃ ādiyati."
msgstr "whoever, intending to steal, takes anything having a value of five <i lang=\"pli\">māsaka</i> coins or more than five <i lang=\"pli\">māsaka</i> coins that has not been given—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:34.3"
msgid "Eso coro nāma."
msgstr "he is called “a thief.”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="31"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.221"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:35.1"
msgid "Haneyyuṃ vāti"
msgstr "Would beat:"

#. </strong>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:35.2"
msgid "hatthena vā pādena vā kasāya vā vettena vā aḍḍhadaṇḍakena vā chejjāya vā haneyyuṃ."
msgstr "would beat with the hand, the foot, a whip, a cane, a cudgel, or by mutilation."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="32"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.222"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:36.1"
msgid "Bandheyyuṃ vāti "
msgstr "Would […] imprison:"

#. </strong>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:36.2"
msgid "rajju­bandha­nena vā andubandhanena vā saṅ­kha­lika­bandha­nena vā ghara­bandha­nena vā nagara­bandha­nena vā gāmabandhanena vā nigama­bandha­nena vā bandheyyuṃ, purisaguttiṃ vā kareyyuṃ."
msgstr "would imprison by constriction with a rope, by constriction with shackles, by constriction with chains, by constriction to a house, by constriction to a city, by constriction to a village, by constriction to a town, by being guarded."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="33"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.223"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:37.1"
msgid "Pabbājeyyuṃ vāti"
msgstr "Would […] banish:"

#. </strong>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:37.2"
msgid "gāmā vā nigamā vā nagarā vā janapadā vā janapadapadesā vā pabbājeyyuṃ."
msgstr "would banish from a village, from a town, from a city, from a country, or from a district."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="34"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.224"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:38.1"
msgid "Corosi bālosi mūḷhosi thenosīti"
msgstr "You’re a bandit, you’re a fool, you’ve gone astray, you’re a thief:"

#. </strong>
#. <span class="note" hidden>Because I have not tried to replicate the structure of the Pali—in this case the subordinate/demonstrative clause structure and the resulting repetitiveness—the next two terms defined in the Pali have no counterpart in my translation. But no information is lost since both terms have already been defined earlier. The two terms in question are <i lang="pli">tathārūpaṃ</i>, which is defined in exactly the same way as <i lang="pli">yathārūpaṃ</i>, “the sort,” and secondly, <i lang="pli">ādiyamāno</i>, which is defined in exactly the same way as <i lang="pli">ādiyeyya</i>, “takes.”</span>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:38.2"
msgid "paribhāso eso."
msgstr "this is a rebuke."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="35"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:39.1"
msgid "Tathārūpaṃ nāma"
msgstr ""

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:39.2"
msgid "pādaṃ vā pādārahaṃ vā atirekapādaṃ vā."
msgstr ""

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="36"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:40.1"
msgid "Ādiyamānoti"
msgstr ""

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:40.2"
msgid "ādiyamāno haramāno avaharamāno iriyāpathaṃ vikopayamāno ṭhānā cāvayamāno saṅketaṃ vītināmayamāno."
msgstr ""

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="37"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.227"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:41.1"
msgid "Ayampīti"
msgstr "He too:"

#. </strong>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:41.2"
msgid "purimaṃ upādāya vuccati."
msgstr "this is said with reference to the preceding offense entailing expulsion."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="38"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.228"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:42.1"
msgid "Pārājiko hotīti"
msgstr "Is expelled:"

#. </strong>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
#. VAR: pavutto → pamutto (pts1) | pavuttho (itipi)
#. VAR: haritatthāya → haritattāya (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:42.2"
msgid "seyyathāpi nāma paṇḍupalāso bandhanā pavutto abhabbo haritatthāya;"
msgstr "just as a fallen, withered leaf is incapable of becoming green again,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:42.3"
msgid "evameva bhikkhu pādaṃ vā pādārahaṃ vā atirekapādaṃ vā adinnaṃ they­ya­saṅ­khā­taṃ ādiyitvā assamaṇo hoti asakyaputtiyo."
msgstr " so too a monk who, intending to steal, takes a <i lang=\"pli\">pāda</i> coin, the worth of a <i lang=\"pli\">pāda</i>, or more than a <i lang=\"pli\">pāda</i> that had not been given to him, is not an ascetic, not a son of the Sakyan—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:42.4"
msgid "Tena vuccati—"
msgstr "therefore it is said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:42.5"
msgid "“pārājiko hotī”ti."
msgstr "“he is expelled.”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="39"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.229"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:43.1"
msgid "Asaṃvāsoti"
msgstr "Not in communion:"

#. </strong>
#. <span class="gloss"><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:43.2"
msgid "saṃvāso nāma"
msgstr "Communion:"

#. </strong>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:43.3"
msgid "ekakammaṃ ekuddeso samasikkhatā."
msgstr "common formal procedures, the same recital, the same training—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:43.4"
msgid "Eso saṃvāso nāma."
msgstr "this is called “communion.”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:43.5"
msgid "So tena saddhiṃ natthi."
msgstr "He does not take part in this—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:43.6"
msgid "Tena vuccati—“asaṃvāso”ti."
msgstr "therefore it is called “not in communion.”"

#. </span>
#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:44.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:44.2"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations part 1"

#. </h3><h4>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:44.3"
msgid ""
msgstr "Summary"

#. </h4><p><a class="sc" id="40"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="Bu-Pj.2.4"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.2.4.1"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.230"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.76"></a> 
#. VAR: vanappati → vanaspati (bj)
#. VAR: dantapoṇaṃ → dantaponaṃ (bj, mr)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:44.4"
msgid "Bhūmaṭṭhaṃ thalaṭṭhaṃ ākāsaṭṭhaṃ vehāsaṭṭhaṃ udakaṭṭhaṃ nāvaṭṭhaṃ yānaṭṭhaṃ bhāraṭṭhaṃ ārāmaṭṭhaṃ vihāraṭṭhaṃ khettaṭṭhaṃ vatthuṭṭhaṃ gāmaṭṭhaṃ araññaṭṭhaṃ udakaṃ dantapoṇaṃ vanappati haraṇakaṃ upanidhi suṅkaghātaṃ pāṇo apadaṃ dvipadaṃ catuppadaṃ bahuppadaṃ ocarako oṇirakkho saṃvidāvahāro saṅketakammaṃ nimitta­kammanti."
msgstr "Being in the earth, being on the ground, being inthe air, being above ground, being in water, being in a boat, being in a vehicle, carried as a burden, being in a park, being in a monastic dwelling, being in a field, being on a plot of land, being in a village, being in the wilderness, water, toothbrush, forest tree, that which is carried, that which is deposited, customs station, a living being, footless, two-footed, four-footed, many-footed, a spy, a keeper of entrusted property, a mutually agreed theft, an arranged action, the making of a sign."

#. </p><h4>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:45.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Exposition"

#. </h4><p><a class="sc" id="41"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.2.4.2"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.231"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:45.2"
msgid "Bhūmaṭṭhaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Being in the earth:"

#. </strong>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:45.3"
msgid "bhaṇḍaṃ bhūmiyaṃ nikkhittaṃ hoti nikhātaṃ paṭicchannaṃ."
msgstr "the goods have been put down into the earth, buried, covered."

#. </span>
#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.77"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:45.4"
msgid "Bhūmaṭṭhaṃ bhaṇḍaṃ avaharissāmīti theyyacitto dutiyaṃ vā pariyesati kudālaṃ vā piṭakaṃ vā pariyesati gacchati vā,"
msgstr "If, intending to steal, he thinks, “I’ll take the goods in the earth,” and he seeks for a companion, or he seeks for a hoe or a basket, or he just goes to the goods,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:45.5"
msgid "āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.48"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:45.6"
msgid "Tattha jātakaṃ kaṭṭhaṃ vā lataṃ vā chindati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he breaks a piece of wood or a creeper growing there, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. VAR: byūhati → vyūhati (bj, pts1) | viyūhati (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:45.7"
msgid "Tattha paṃsuṃ khaṇati vā byūhati vā uddharati vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he digs the soil or piles it up or removes it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:45.8"
msgid "Kumbhiṃ āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he touches the container, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:45.9"
msgid "Phandāpeti, āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "If he makes it quiver, he commits a serious offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:45.10"
msgid "Ṭhānā cāveti, āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "If he makes it move from its base, he commits an offense entailing expulsion."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:45.11"
msgid "Attano bhājanaṃ pavesetvā pañcamāsakaṃ vā ati­reka­pañca­māsakaṃ vā agghanakaṃ theyyacitto āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If, intending to steal, he puts his own vessel into the container and touches something worth five <i lang=\"pli\">māsaka</i> coins or more than five <i lang=\"pli\">māsakas</i>, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:45.12"
msgid "Phandāpeti, āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "If he makes it quiver, he commits a serious offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:45.13"
msgid "Attano bhājanagataṃ vā karoti muṭṭhiṃ vā chindati, āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "If he makes it enter his own vessel or takes it with his fist, there is an offense entailing expulsion."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.78"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:45.14"
msgid "Suttāruḷhaṃ bhaṇḍaṃ pāmaṅgaṃ vā kaṇṭhasuttakaṃ vā kaṭisuttakaṃ vā sāṭakaṃ vā veṭhanaṃ vā theyyacitto āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If, intending to steal, he touches goods held together by a string, or a bracelet, a necklace, an ornamental girdle, a robe, or a turban, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:45.15"
msgid "Phandāpeti, āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "If he makes it quiver, he commits a serious offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:45.16"
msgid "Koṭiyaṃ gahetvā uccāreti, āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "If he grasps it at the top and pulls it, he commits a serious offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:45.17"
msgid "Ghaṃsanto nīharati, āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "If, while stroking it, he lifts it, he commits a serious offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:45.18"
msgid "Antamaso kesag­gamattampi kumbhimukhā moceti, āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "If he removes the goods even as much as a hair’s breadth over the rim of the container, he commits an offense entailing expulsion."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:45.19"
msgid "Sappiṃ vā telaṃ vā madhuṃ vā phāṇitaṃ vā pañcamāsakaṃ vā ati­reka­pañca­māsakaṃ vā agghanakaṃ theyyacitto ekena payogena pivati, āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "If, intending to steal, he drinks—in a single action—ghee, oil, honey, or molasses having a value of five <i lang=\"pli\">māsaka</i> coins or more than five <i lang=\"pli\">māsakas</i>, he commits an offense entailing expulsion."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:45.20"
msgid "Tattheva bhindati vā"
msgstr "If he destroys it,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:45.21"
msgid "chaḍḍeti vā"
msgstr "throws it away,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:45.22"
msgid "jhāpeti vā"
msgstr "burns it,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:45.23"
msgid "aparibhogaṃ vā karoti"
msgstr "or renders it useless,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:45.24"
msgid "āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="42"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.2.4.3"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.232"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:46.1"
msgid "Thalaṭṭhaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Being on the ground:"

#. </strong>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:46.2"
msgid "bhaṇḍaṃ thale nikkhittaṃ hoti."
msgstr "the goods have been put down on the ground."

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:46.3"
msgid "Thalaṭṭhaṃ bhaṇḍaṃ avaharissāmīti theyyacitto dutiyaṃ vā pariyesati gacchati vā,"
msgstr "If, intending to steal, he thinks, “I’ll steal the goods on the ground,” and he either searches for a companion or just goes there himself,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:46.4"
msgid "āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.79"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:46.5"
msgid "Āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he touches them, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:46.6"
msgid "Phandāpeti, āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "If he makes them quiver, he commits a serious offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:46.7"
msgid "Ṭhānā cāveti, āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "If he moves them from their base, he commits an offense entailing expulsion."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="43"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.2.4.4"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.233"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:47.1"
msgid "Ākāsaṭṭhaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Being in the air:"

#. </strong>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:47.2"
msgid "bhaṇḍaṃ ākāsagataṃ hoti."
msgstr "the goods are in the air—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:47.3"
msgid "Moro vā kapiñjaro vā tittiro vā vaṭṭako vā,"
msgstr "a peacock, a partridge, or a quail;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:47.4"
msgid "sāṭakaṃ vā veṭhanaṃ vā hiraññaṃ vā suvaṇṇaṃ vā chijjamānaṃ patati."
msgstr "or a robe, a turban, or gold that falls after being cut loose."

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:47.5"
msgid "Ākāsaṭṭhaṃ bhaṇḍaṃ avaharissāmīti theyyacitto dutiyaṃ vā pariyesati gacchati vā,"
msgstr "If, intending to steal, he thinks, “I’ll steal the goods in the air,” and he either searches for a companion or just goes there himself,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:47.6"
msgid "āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:47.7"
msgid "Gamanaṃ upacchindati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he cuts off their course of movement, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:47.8"
msgid "Āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he touches them, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:47.9"
msgid "Phandāpeti, āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "If he makes them quiver, he commits a serious offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:47.10"
msgid "Ṭhānā cāveti, āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "If he moves them from their base, he commits an offense entailing expulsion."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="44"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.2.4.5"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.234"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:48.1"
msgid "Vehāsaṭṭhaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Being above ground:"

#. </strong>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:48.2"
msgid "bhaṇḍaṃ vehāsagataṃ hoti."
msgstr "the goods are above ground—"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.80"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:48.3"
msgid "Mañce vā pīṭhe vā cīvaravaṃse vā cīvararajjuyā vā bhittikhile vā nāgadante vā rukkhe vā laggitaṃ hoti, antamaso pattādhārakepi."
msgstr "on a bed, on a bench, on a bamboo robe-rack, on a clothes line for robes, on a peg in the wall, on an elephant-tusk peg, in a tree, or even just fastened to a bowl stand."

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:48.4"
msgid "Vehāsaṭṭhaṃ bhaṇḍaṃ avaharissāmīti theyyacitto dutiyaṃ vā pariyesati gacchati vā,"
msgstr "If, intending to steal, he thinks, “I’ll steal the goods that are above ground,” and he either searches for a companion or just goes there himself,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:48.5"
msgid "āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:48.6"
msgid "Āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he touches them, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:48.7"
msgid "Phandāpeti, āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "If he makes them quiver, he commits a serious offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:48.8"
msgid "Ṭhānā cāveti, āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "If he moves them from their base, he commits an offense entailing expulsion."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="45"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.2.4.6"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.49"></a> <a class="ms-pa" id="ms.235"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:49.1"
msgid "Udakaṭṭhaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Being in the water:"

#. </strong>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:49.2"
msgid "bhaṇḍaṃ udake nikkhittaṃ hoti."
msgstr "the goods have been deposited in the water."

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:49.3"
msgid "Udakaṭṭhaṃ bhaṇḍaṃ avaharissāmīti theyyacitto dutiyaṃ vā pariyesati gacchati vā,"
msgstr "If, intending to steal, he thinks, “I’ll steal the goods in the water,” and he either searches for a companion or just goes there himself,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:49.4"
msgid "āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:49.5"
msgid "Nimujjati vā ummujjati vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "He either dives into the water or floats on the surface, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:49.6"
msgid "Āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he touches the goods, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:49.7"
msgid "Phandāpeti, āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "If he makes them quiver, he commits a serious offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:49.8"
msgid "Ṭhānā cāveti, āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "If he moves them from their base, he commits an offense entailing expulsion."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:49.9"
msgid "Tattha jātakaṃ uppalaṃ vā padumaṃ vā puṇḍarīkaṃ vā bhisaṃ vā macchaṃ vā kacchapaṃ vā pañcamāsakaṃ vā ati­reka­pañca­māsakaṃ vā agghanakaṃ theyyacitto āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If, intending to steal, he touches either a blue, red, or white lotus growing there, or the sprout of a lotus, or a fish, or a turtle having a value of five <i lang=\"pli\">māsakas</i> or more than five <i lang=\"pli\">māsakas</i>, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:49.10"
msgid "Phandāpeti, āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "If he makes them quiver, he commits a serious offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:49.11"
msgid "Ṭhānā cāveti, āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "If he moves them from their base, he commits an offense entailing expulsion."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="46"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.2.4.7"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.236"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:50.1"
msgid "Nāvā nāma"
msgstr "A boat:"

#. </strong>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:50.2"
msgid "yāya tarati."
msgstr "that by mean of which one crosses."

#. </span>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:50.3"
msgid "Nāvaṭṭhaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Being in a boat:"

#. </strong>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:50.4"
msgid "bhaṇḍaṃ nāvāya nikkhittaṃ hoti."
msgstr "the goods have been deposited in a boat."

#. </span>
#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.81"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:50.5"
msgid "“Nāvaṭṭhaṃ bhaṇḍaṃ avaharissāmī”ti theyyacitto dutiyaṃ vā pariyesati gacchati vā,"
msgstr "If, intending to steal, he thinks, “I’ll steal the goods in the boat,” and he either searches for a companion or just goes there himself,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:50.6"
msgid "āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:50.7"
msgid "Āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he touches them, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:50.8"
msgid "Phandāpeti, āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "If he makes them quiver, he commits a serious offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:50.9"
msgid "Ṭhānā cāveti, āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "If he moves them from their base, he commits an offense entailing expulsion."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:50.10"
msgid "Nāvaṃ avaharissāmīti theyyacitto dutiyaṃ vā pariyesati gacchati vā,"
msgstr "If, intending to steal, he thinks, “I’ll steal the boat,” and he either searches for a companion or just goes there himself,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:50.11"
msgid "āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:50.12"
msgid "Āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he touches it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:50.13"
msgid "Phandāpeti, āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "If he makes it quiver, he commits a serious offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:50.14"
msgid "Bandhanaṃ moceti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he loosens the moorings, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:50.15"
msgid "Bandhanaṃ mocetvā āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If, after loosening the moorings, he touches it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:50.16"
msgid "Phandāpeti, āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "If he makes it quiver, he commits a serious offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:50.17"
msgid "Uddhaṃ vā adho vā tiriyaṃ vā antamaso kesag­gamattampi saṅkāmeti, āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "If he makes it move up or down or across the water, even as much as a hair’s breadth, he commits an offense entailing expulsion."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="47"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.2.4.8"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.237"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:51.1"
msgid "Yānaṃ nāma"
msgstr "A vehicle:"

#. </strong>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:51.2"
msgid "vayhaṃ ratho sakaṭaṃ sandamānikā."
msgstr "a wagon, a carriage, a cart, a chariot."

#. </span>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:51.3"
msgid "Yānaṭṭhaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Being in a vehicle:"

#. </strong>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:51.4"
msgid "bhaṇḍaṃ yāne nikkhittaṃ hoti."
msgstr "the goods have been deposited in a vehicle."

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:51.5"
msgid "Yānaṭṭhaṃ bhaṇḍaṃ avaharissāmīti theyyacitto dutiyaṃ vā pariyesati gacchati vā,"
msgstr "If, intending to steal, he thinks, “I’ll steal the goods in the vehicle,” and he either searches for a companion or just goes there himself,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:51.6"
msgid "āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

