msgid "Phandāpeti, āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "If he makes them quiver, he commits a serious offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:51.9"
msgid "Ṭhānā cāveti, āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "If he moves them from their base, he commits an offense entailing expulsion."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:51.10"
msgid "Yānaṃ avaharissāmīti theyyacitto dutiyaṃ vā pariyesati gacchati vā,"
msgstr "If, intending to steal, he thinks, “I’ll steal the vehicle,” and he either searches for a companion or just goes there himself,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:51.11"
msgid "āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:51.12"
msgid "Āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he touches it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:51.13"
msgid "Phandāpeti, āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "If he makes it quiver, he commits a serious offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:51.14"
msgid "Ṭhānā cāveti, āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "If he moves it from its base, he commits an offense entailing expulsion."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="48"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.2.4.9"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.238"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:52.1"
msgid "Bhāro nāma"
msgstr "A burden:"

#. </strong>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:52.2"
msgid "sīsabhāro khandhabhāro kaṭibhāro olambako."
msgstr "a burden carried on the head, a burden carried on the shoulder, a burden carried on the hip, one hanging down."

#. </span>
#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.82"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:52.3"
msgid "Sīse bhāraṃ theyyacitto āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If, intending to steal, he touches the burden on the head, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:52.4"
msgid "Phandāpeti, āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "If he makes it quiver, he commits a serious offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:52.5"
msgid "Khandhaṃ oropeti, āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "If he lowers it to the shoulder, he commits an offense entailing expulsion."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:52.6"
msgid "Khandhe bhāraṃ theyyacitto āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If, intending to steal, he touches the burden on the shoulder, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:52.7"
msgid "Phandāpeti, āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "If he makes it quiver, he commits a serious offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:52.8"
msgid "Kaṭiṃ oropeti, āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "If he lowers it to the hip, he commits an offense entailing expulsion."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:52.9"
msgid "Kaṭiyā bhāraṃ theyyacitto āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If, intending to steal, he touches the burden on the hip, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:52.10"
msgid "Phandāpeti, āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "If he causes it to quiver, he commits a serious offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:52.11"
msgid "Hatthena gaṇhāti, āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "If he takes it with a hand, there is an offense entailing expulsion."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:52.12"
msgid "Hatthe bhāraṃ theyyacitto bhūmiyaṃ nikkhipati, āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "If, intending to steal a burden in the hand, he deposits it on the ground, he commits an offense entailing expulsion."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:52.13"
msgid "Theyyacitto bhūmito gaṇhāti, āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "If, intending to steal, he takes it from the ground, he commits an offense entailing expulsion."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="49"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.2.4.10"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.239"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:53.1"
msgid "Ārāmo nāma"
msgstr "A park:"

#. </strong>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:53.2"
msgid "pupphārāmo phalārāmo."
msgstr "a park with flowers, an orchard."

#. </span>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:53.3"
msgid "Ārāmaṭṭhaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Being in a park:"

#. </strong>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:53.4"
msgid "bhaṇḍaṃ ārāme catūhi ṭhānehi nikkhittaṃ hoti—"
msgstr "the goods have been deposited in a park in four places:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:53.5"
msgid "bhūmaṭṭhaṃ thalaṭṭhaṃ, ākāsaṭṭhaṃ, vehāsaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr "in the earth, on the ground, in the air, above the ground."

#. </span>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.50"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:53.6"
msgid "Ārāmaṭṭhaṃ bhaṇḍaṃ avaharissāmīti theyyacitto dutiyaṃ vā pariyesati gacchati vā,"
msgstr "If, intending to steal, he thinks, “I’ll steal the goods in the park,” and he either searches for a companion or just goes there himself,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:53.7"
msgid "āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:53.8"
msgid "Āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he touches them, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:53.9"
msgid "Phandāpeti, āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "If he makes them quiver, he commits a serious offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:53.10"
msgid "Ṭhānā cāveti, āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "If he moves them from their base, he commits an offense entailing expulsion."

#. </p><p>
