#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:60.2"
msgid "chinnaṃ vā acchinnaṃ vā."
msgstr "either ready for use or not."

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:60.3"
msgid "Pañcamāsakaṃ vā ati­reka­pañca­māsakaṃ vā agghanakaṃ theyyacitto āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If, intending to steal, he touches what has a value of five <i lang=\"pli\">māsaka</i> coins or more than five <i lang=\"pli\">māsakas</i>, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:60.4"
msgid "Phandāpeti, āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "If he makes it quiver, he commits a serious offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:60.5"
msgid "Ṭhānā cāveti, āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "If he moves it from its base, he commits an offense entailing expulsion."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="57"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.2.4.18"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.86"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.247"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:61.1"
msgid "Vanappati nāma"
msgstr "Forest tree:"

#. </strong>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:61.2"
msgid "yo manussānaṃ pariggahito hoti rukkho paribhogo."
msgstr "whatever tree is owned by people."

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:61.3"
msgid "Theyyacitto chindati, pahāre pahāre āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If, intending to steal, he fells it, then for each blow he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:61.4"
msgid "Ekaṃ pahāraṃ anāgate, āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "When one blow remains before the tree is felled, he commits a serious offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:61.5"
msgid "Tasmiṃ pahāre āgate, āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "When the last blow is completed, he commits an offense entailing expulsion."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="58"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.2.4.19"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.248"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:62.1"
msgid "Haraṇakaṃ"
msgstr "Goods being carried:"

#. </strong>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:62.2"
msgid "nāma aññassa haraṇakaṃ bhaṇḍaṃ."
msgstr "the goods of another are being carried."

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:62.3"
msgid "Theyyacitto āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If, intending to steal, he touches them, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:62.4"
msgid "Phandāpeti, āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "If he makes them quiver, he commits a serious offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:62.5"
msgid "Ṭhānā cāveti, āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "If he moves them from their base, he commits an offense entailing expulsion."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:62.6"
msgid "Saha­bhaṇḍa­hārakaṃ padasā nessāmīti paṭhamaṃ pādaṃ saṅkāmeti, āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "If he thinks, “Together with the carrier I’ll carry off the goods,” and he makes the carrier move one foot, he commits a serious offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:62.7"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ pādaṃ saṅkāmeti, āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "If he makes him move the second foot, he commits an offense entailing expulsion."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:62.8"
msgid "Patitaṃ bhaṇḍaṃ gahessāmīti pātāpeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he thinks, “I’ll take the fallen goods,” and he makes them fall, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:62.9"
msgid "Patitaṃ bhaṇḍaṃ pañcamāsakaṃ vā ati­reka­pañca­māsakaṃ vā agghanakaṃ theyyacitto āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If, intending to steal, he touches fallen goods having a value of five <i lang=\"pli\">māsaka</i> coins or more than five <i lang=\"pli\">māsakas</i>, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:62.10"
msgid "Phandāpeti, āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "If he makes them quiver, he commits a serious offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:62.11"
msgid "Ṭhānā cāveti, āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "If he moves them from their base, he commits an offense entailing expulsion."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="59"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.2.4.20"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.249"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:63.1"
msgid "Upanidhi"
msgstr "Deposit:"

#. </strong>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:63.2"
msgid "upanikkhittaṃ bhaṇḍaṃ."
msgstr "goods deposited with a monk."

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:63.3"
msgid "Dehi me bhaṇḍanti vuccamāno nāhaṃ gaṇhāmīti bhaṇati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he is told, “Give me my goods,” and he says, “I’m not getting them,” he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. <span class="note" hidden>The Pali text just says that he evokes doubt in the mind of the owner, <i lang="pli">sāmikassa vimatiṃ uppādeti</i>. That the doubt refers to the possibility of getting the goods back is supplied from the commentary, see <span class="ref">Sp.2.350.1</span>: <i lang="pli">‘Dassati nu kho me no’ti sāmiko vimatiṃ uppādeti</i>.</span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:63.4"
msgid "Sāmikassa vimatiṃ uppādeti, āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "If he evokes doubt in the mind of the owner as to whether he will get them back, he commits a serious offense."

#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.52"></a>"
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:63.5"
msgid "Sāmiko na mayhaṃ dassatīti dhuraṃ nikkhipati, āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "If the owner thinks, “He won’t give them to me,” and he gives up the effort of getting them back, he commits an offense entailing expulsion."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:63.6"
msgid "Dhammaṃ caranto sāmikaṃ parājeti, āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "If he resorts to the law and defeats the owner, he commits an offense entailing expulsion."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:63.7"
msgid "Dhammaṃ caranto parajjati, āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "If he resorts to the law but is defeated, he commits a serious offense."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="60"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.2.4.21"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.250"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:64.1"
msgid "Suṅkaghātaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Customs station:"

#. </strong>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:64.2"
msgid "raññā ṭhapitaṃ hoti pabbatakhaṇḍe vā nadītitthe vā gāmadvāre vā—"
msgstr "it is established by a king in a mountain-pass, at a ford in a river, or at the gateway of a village"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:64.3"
msgid "“atra paviṭṭhassa suṅkaṃ gaṇhantū”ti."
msgstr "so that tax can be collected from a person passing through."

#. <span class="note" hidden>Although not explicitly stated in the Pali, the commentary, <span class="ref">Sp.2.358.29</span>, confirms that the value meant is the tax value: “Goods having a value to the king means: goods having a worth to the king. The meaning is: the goods because of which tax having a value of five <i lang="pli">māsakas</i> or more is to be given to the king.” (<i lang="pli">Rājaggaṃ bhaṇḍanti: rājārahaṃ bhaṇḍaṃ; yato rañño pañcamāsakaṃ vā atirekapañcamāsakaṃ vā agghanakaṃ suṅkaṃ dātabbaṃ hoti, taṃ bhaṇḍanti attho</i>.)</span> 
#. VAR: rājaggaṃ → rājagghaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:64.4"
msgid "Tatra pavisitvā rājaggaṃ bhaṇḍaṃ pañcamāsakaṃ vā ati­reka­pañca­māsakaṃ vā agghanakaṃ theyyacitto āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If, intending to steal and having entered the customs station, he touches goods that have a tax value to the king of five <i lang=\"pli\">māsaka</i> coins or more than five <i lang=\"pli\">māsakas</i>, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:64.5"
msgid "Phandāpeti, āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "If he makes them quiver, he commits a serious offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:64.6"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ pādaṃ suṅkaghātaṃ atikkāmeti, āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "If he goes beyond the customs station with one foot, he commits a serious offense."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.87"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:64.7"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ pādaṃ atikkāmeti, āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "If he goes beyond the customs station with the second foot, he commits an offense entailing expulsion."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:64.8"
msgid "Antosuṅkaghāte ṭhito bahi­suṅ­kaghātaṃ pāteti, āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "If, standing within the customs station, he makes the goods fall outside the customs station, he commits an offense entailing expulsion."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:64.9"
msgid "Suṅkaṃ pariharati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he avoids the customs station altogether, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="61"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.2.4.22"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.251"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:65.1"
msgid "Pāṇo nāma"
msgstr "Creature:"

#. </strong>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:65.2"
msgid "manussapāṇo vuccati."
msgstr "a human being is what is meant."

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:65.3"
msgid "Theyyacitto āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If, intending to steal, he touches the person, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:65.4"
msgid "Phandāpeti, āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "If he makes the person quiver, he commits a serious offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:65.5"
msgid "Ṭhānā cāveti, āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "If he moves the person from their base, he commits an offense entailing expulsion."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:65.6"
msgid "Padasā nessāmīti paṭhamaṃ pādaṃ saṅkāmeti, āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "If he thinks, “I’ll take the person away on foot,” and he makes them move the first foot, he commits a serious offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:65.7"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ pādaṃ saṅkāmeti, āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "If he makes them move the second foot, he commits an offense entailing expulsion."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="62"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.2.4.23"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.252"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:66.1"
msgid "Apadaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Footless:"

#. </strong>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:66.2"
msgid "ahi macchā."
msgstr "snakes and fish."

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:66.3"
msgid "Pañcamāsakaṃ vā ati­reka­pañca­māsakaṃ vā agghanakaṃ theyyacitto āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If, intending to steal, he touches what has a value of five <i lang=\"pli\">māsaka</i> coins or more than five <i lang=\"pli\">māsakas</i>, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:66.4"
msgid "Phandāpeti, āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "If he makes them quiver, he commits a serious offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:66.5"
msgid "Ṭhānā cāveti, āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "If he moves them from their base, he commits an offense entailing expulsion."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="63"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.2.4.24"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.253"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:67.1"
msgid "Dvipadaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Two-footed:"

#. </strong>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:67.2"
msgid "manussā, pakkhajātā."
msgstr "humans and birds."

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:67.3"
msgid "Theyyacitto āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If, intending to steal, he touches it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:67.4"
msgid "Phandāpeti, āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "If he makes it quiver, he commits a serious offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:67.5"
msgid "Ṭhānā cāveti, āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "If he moves it from its base, he commits an offense entailing expulsion."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:67.6"
msgid "Padasā nessāmīti paṭhamaṃ pādaṃ saṅkāmeti, āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "If he thinks, “I’ll take it away on foot,” and he makes it move the first foot, he commits a serious offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:67.7"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ pādaṃ saṅkāmeti, āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "If he makes it move the second foot, he commits an offense entailing expulsion."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="64"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.2.4.25"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.254"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:68.1"
msgid "Catuppadaṃ nāma—"
msgstr "Four-footed:"

#. </strong>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:68.2"
msgid "hatthī assā oṭṭhā goṇā gadrabhā pasukā."
msgstr "elephants, horses, camels, cattle, asses, domesticated animals."

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:68.3"
msgid "Theyyacitto āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If, intending to steal, he touches it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:68.4"
msgid "Phandāpeti, āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "If he makes it quiver, he commits a serious offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:68.5"
msgid "Ṭhānā cāveti, āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "If he moves it from its base, he commits an offense entailing expulsion."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.88"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:68.6"
msgid "Padasā nessāmīti paṭhamaṃ pādaṃ saṅkāmeti, āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "If he thinks, “I’ll take it away on foot,” and he makes it move the first foot, he commits a serious offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:68.7"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ pādaṃ saṅkāmeti, āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "If he makes it move the second foot, he commits a serious offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:68.8"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ pādaṃ saṅkāmeti, āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "If he makes it move the third foot, he commits a serious offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:68.9"
msgid "Catutthaṃ pādaṃ saṅkāmeti, āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "If he makes it move the fourth foot, he commits an offense entailing expulsion."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="65"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.2.4.26"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.255"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:69.1"
msgid "Bahuppadaṃ nāma—"
msgstr "Many-footed:"

#. </strong>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:69.2"
msgid "vicchikā satapadī uccāliṅ­ga­pāṇakā."
msgstr "scorpions, centipedes, caterpillars."

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:69.3"
msgid "Pañcamāsakaṃ vā ati­reka­pañca­māsakaṃ vā agghanakaṃ theyyacitto āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If, intending to steal, he touches what has a value of five <i lang=\"pli\">māsaka</i> coins or more than five <i lang=\"pli\">māsakas</i>, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:69.4"
msgid "Phandāpeti, āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "If he makes it quiver, he commits a serious offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:69.5"
msgid "Ṭhānā cāveti, āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "If he moves it from its base, he commits an offense entailing expulsion."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:69.6"
msgid "Padasā nessāmīti saṅkāmeti, pade pade āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "If he thinks, “I’ll take it away on foot,” and he makes it move, he commits a serious offense for each leg that moves."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:69.7"
msgid "Pacchimaṃ pādaṃ saṅkāmeti, āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "When the last leg moves, he commits an offense entailing expulsion."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="66"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.2.4.27"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.256"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:70.1"
msgid "Ocarako nāma"
msgstr "A spy:"

#. </strong>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:70.2"
msgid "bhaṇḍaṃ ocaritvā ācikkhati—"
msgstr "having spied out goods. If he describes them and says,"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:70.3"
msgid "“itthannāmaṃ bhaṇḍaṃ avaharā”ti,"
msgstr "“Steal such-and-such goods,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:70.4"
msgid "āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:70.5"
msgid "So taṃ bhaṇḍaṃ avaharati, āpatti ubhinnaṃ pārājikassa."
msgstr "If he makes it quiver, he commits a serious offense."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="67"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.2.4.28"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.53"></a> <a class="ms-pa" id="ms.257"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:71.1"
msgid "Oṇirakkho nāma"
msgstr "A protector of goods:"

#. </strong>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:71.2"
msgid "āhaṭaṃ bhaṇḍaṃ gopento"
msgstr "a monk who guards goods that have been brought to him."

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:71.3"
msgid "pañcamāsakaṃ vā ati­reka­pañca­māsakaṃ vā agghanakaṃ theyyacitto āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If, intending to steal, he touches what has a value of five <i lang=\"pli\">māsaka</i> coins or more than five <i lang=\"pli\">māsakas</i>, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:71.4"
msgid "Phandāpeti, āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "If he makes them quiver, he commits a serious offense."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:71.5"
msgid "Ṭhānā cāveti, āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "If he moves them from their base, he commits an offense entailing expulsion."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="68"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.2.4.29"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.258"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:72.1"
msgid "Saṃvidāvahāro nāma"
msgstr "A mutually agreed theft:"

#. </strong>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:72.2"
msgid "sambahulā saṃvidahitvā"
msgstr "many have agreed together."

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:72.3"
msgid "eko bhaṇḍaṃ avaharati, āpatti sabbesaṃ pārājikassa."
msgstr "If only one steals the goods, there is an offense entailing expulsion for all of them."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="69"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.2.4.30"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.259"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:73.1"
msgid "Saṅketakammaṃ nāma"
msgstr "An arranged action:"

#. </strong>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:73.2"
msgid "saṅketaṃ karoti—"
msgstr "one makes an arrangement"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:73.3"
msgid "“purebhattaṃ vā pacchābhattaṃ vā rattiṃ vā divā vā"
msgstr "for before the meal or for after the meal, for the night or for the day."

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:73.4"
msgid "tena saṅketena taṃ bhaṇḍaṃ avaharā”ti,"
msgstr "If he says, “Take those goods according to this agreement,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:73.5"
msgid "āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.89"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:73.6"
msgid "Tena saṅketena taṃ bhaṇḍaṃ avaharati, āpatti ubhinnaṃ pārājikassa."
msgstr "If the other takes those goods according to that agreement, there is an offense entailing expulsion for both."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:73.7"
msgid "Taṃ saṅketaṃ pure vā pacchā vā taṃ bhaṇḍaṃ avaharati, mūlaṭṭhassa anāpatti."
msgstr "If he takes those goods before or after the time of the agreement, there is no offense for the instigator,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:73.8"
msgid "Avahārakassa āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "but an offense entailing expulsion for the thief."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="70"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.2.4.31"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.260"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:74.1"
msgid "Nimittakammaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Making a sign:"

#. </strong>
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:74.2"
msgid "nimittaṃ karoti."
msgstr "he makes a sign."

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:74.3"
msgid "Akkhiṃ vā nikhaṇissāmi bhamukaṃ vā ukkhipissāmi sīsaṃ vā ukkhipissāmi, tena nimittena taṃ bhaṇḍaṃ avaharāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he says, “When I wink/raise my eyebrow/nod, at that sign, steal the goods,” he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:74.4"
msgid "Tena nimittena taṃ bhaṇḍaṃ avaharati, āpatti ubhinnaṃ pārājikassa."
msgstr "If, at that sign, the other steals the goods, there is an offense entailing expulsion for both."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:74.5"
msgid "Taṃ nimittaṃ pure vā pacchā vā taṃ bhaṇḍaṃ avaharati, mūlaṭṭhassa anāpatti."
msgstr "If he steals the goods before or after the sign, there is no offense for the instigator,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:74.6"
msgid "Avahārakassa āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "but an offense entailing expulsion for the thief."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:75.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations part 2"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="71"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="Bu-Pj.2.5"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.2.5.1"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.261"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:75.2"
msgid "Bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ āṇāpeti—"
msgstr "If a monk tells another monk,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:75.3"
msgid "“itthannāmaṃ bhaṇḍaṃ avaharā”ti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "“Steal such-and-such goods,” he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:75.4"
msgid "So taṃ maññamāno taṃ avaharati, āpatti ubhinnaṃ pārājikassa."
msgstr "If the other monk steals them, thinking they are the ones he has been asked to steal, there is an offense entailing expulsion for both."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="72"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.262"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:76.1"
msgid "Bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ āṇāpeti—"
msgstr "If a monk tells another monk,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:76.2"
msgid "“itthannāmaṃ bhaṇḍaṃ avaharā”ti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr " “Steal such-and-such goods,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:76.3"
msgid "So taṃ maññamāno aññaṃ avaharati,"
msgstr "but the other monk steals something else, thinking they are the ones he has been asked to steal,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:76.4"
msgid "mūlaṭṭhassa anāpatti."
msgstr "there is no offense for the instigator,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:76.5"
msgid "Avahārakassa āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "but there is an offense entailing expulsion for the thief."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="73"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.263"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:77.1"
msgid "Bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ āṇāpeti—"
msgstr "If a monk tells another monk,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:77.2"
msgid "“itthannāmaṃ bhaṇḍaṃ avaharā”ti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "“Steal such-and-such goods,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:77.3"
msgid "So aññaṃ maññamāno taṃ avaharati,"
msgstr " and the other monk steals them, thinking they are something else than what he has been asked to steal,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:77.4"
msgid "āpatti ubhinnaṃ pārājikassa."
msgstr "there is an offense entailing expulsion for both."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="74"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.264"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:78.1"
msgid "Bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ āṇāpeti—"
msgstr "If a monk tells another monk,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:78.2"
msgid "“itthannāmaṃ bhaṇḍaṃ avaharā”ti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "“Steal such-and-such goods,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:78.3"
msgid "So aññaṃ maññamāno aññaṃ avaharati,"
msgstr "but the other monk steals something else, thinking it is something else,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:78.4"
msgid "mūlaṭṭhassa anāpatti."
msgstr "there is no offense for the instigator,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:78.5"
msgid "Avahārakassa āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "but there is an offense entailing expulsion for the thief."

#. </p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="75"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.2.5.2"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.265"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:79.1"
msgid "Bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ āṇāpeti—"
msgstr "If a monk tells another monk,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:79.2"
msgid "“itthannāmassa pāvada—‘itthannāmo itthannāmassa pāvadatu—itthannāmo itthannāmaṃ bhaṇḍaṃ avaharatū’”ti,"
msgstr "“Tell so-and-so to tell so-and-so to steal such-and-such goods,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:79.3"
msgid "āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:79.4"
msgid "So itarassa āroceti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "In informing the next person, there is an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:79.5"
msgid "Avahārako paṭiggaṇhāti, mūlaṭṭhassa āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "If the potential thief agrees, there is a serious offense for the instigator."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:79.6"
msgid "So taṃ bhaṇḍaṃ avaharati, āpatti sabbesaṃ pārājikassa."
msgstr "If he steals those goods, there is an offense entailing expulsion for all of them."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="76"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.266"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.90"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:80.1"
msgid "Bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ āṇāpeti—"
msgstr "If a monk tells another monk,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:80.2"
msgid "“itthannāmassa pāvada—‘itthannāmo itthannāmassa pāvadatu—itthannāmo itthannāmaṃ bhaṇḍaṃ avaharatū’”ti,"
msgstr "“Tell so-and-so to tell so-and-so to steal such-and-such goods,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:80.3"
msgid "āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:80.4"
msgid "So aññaṃ āṇāpeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If the other monk tells someone else than the one he was told to tell, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:80.5"
msgid "Avahārako paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If the potential thief agrees, there is an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:80.6"
msgid "So taṃ bhaṇḍaṃ avaharati, mūlaṭṭhassa anāpatti."
msgstr "If he steals those goods, there is no offense for the instigator,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:80.7"
msgid "Āṇāpakassa ca avahārakassa ca āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "but there is an offense entailing expulsion for the conveyor of the message and the thief."

#. </p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="77"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.2.5.3"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.267"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.54"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:81.1"
msgid "Bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ āṇāpeti—"
msgstr "If a monk tells a second monk,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:81.2"
msgid "“itthannāmaṃ bhaṇḍaṃ avaharā”ti,"
msgstr "“Steal such-and-such goods,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:81.3"
msgid "āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:81.4"
msgid "So gantvā puna paccāgacchati—"
msgstr "If the second monk goes there, but returns, saying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:81.5"
msgid "“nāhaṃ sakkomi taṃ bhaṇḍaṃ avaharitun”ti."
msgstr "“I’m not able to steal those goods,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:81.6"
msgid "So puna āṇāpeti—"
msgstr "and if he tells him again,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:81.7"
msgid "“yadā sakkosi tadā taṃ bhaṇḍaṃ avaharā”ti,"
msgstr "“When you’re able, then steal those goods,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:81.8"
msgid "āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:81.9"
msgid "So taṃ bhaṇḍaṃ avaharati,"
msgstr "If the second monk steals the goods,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:81.10"
msgid "āpatti ubhinnaṃ pārājikassa."
msgstr "there is an offense entailing expulsion for both."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="78"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.2.5.4"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.268"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:82.1"
msgid "Bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ āṇāpeti—"
msgstr "If a monk tells a second monk,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:82.2"
msgid "“itthannāmaṃ bhaṇḍaṃ avaharā”ti,"
msgstr "“Steal such-and-such goods,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:82.3"
msgid "āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:82.4"
msgid "So āṇāpetvā vippaṭisārī na sāveti—"
msgstr "If, after telling him, he regrets it, but does not say to him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:82.5"
msgid "“mā avaharī”ti."
msgstr "“Don’t steal,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:82.6"
msgid "So taṃ bhaṇḍaṃ avaharati,"
msgstr "and the second monk then steals those goods,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:82.7"
msgid "āpatti ubhinnaṃ pārājikassa."
msgstr "there is an offense entailing expulsion for both."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="79"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.269"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:83.1"
msgid "Bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ āṇāpeti—"
msgstr "If a monk tells a second monk,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:83.2"
msgid "“itthannāmaṃ bhaṇḍaṃ avaharā”ti,"
msgstr "“Steal such-and-such goods,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:83.3"
msgid "āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:83.4"
msgid "So āṇāpetvā vippaṭisārī sāveti—"
msgstr "If, after telling him, he regrets it and says,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:83.5"
msgid "“mā avaharī”ti."
msgstr "“Don’t steal,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:83.6"
msgid "So “āṇatto ahaṃ tayā”ti, taṃ bhaṇḍaṃ avaharati,"
msgstr "but the second monk says, “I’ve been told by you to do so,” and he then steals those goods,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:83.7"
msgid "mūlaṭṭhassa anāpatti."
msgstr "there is no offense for the instigator,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:83.8"
msgid "Avahārakassa āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "but an offense entailing expulsion for the thief."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="80"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.270"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:84.1"
msgid "Bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ āṇāpeti—"
msgstr "If a monk tells a second monk,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:84.2"
msgid "“itthannāmaṃ bhaṇḍaṃ avaharā”ti,"
msgstr "“Steal such-and-such goods,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:84.3"
msgid "āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:84.4"
msgid "So āṇāpetvā vippaṭisārī sāveti—"
msgstr "If, after telling him, he regrets it and says to him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:84.5"
msgid "“mā avaharī”ti."
msgstr "“Don’t steal,”"

#. VAR: sādhū”ti → suṭṭhūti (bj, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:84.6"
msgid "So “sādhū”ti?"
msgstr "and the second monk says, “Very well,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:84.7"
msgid "Oramati, ubhinnaṃ anāpatti."
msgstr "and desists, there is no offense for either."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:85.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations part 3"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="81"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="Bu-Pj.2.6"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.2.6.1"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.271"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:85.2"
msgid "Pañcahi ākārehi adinnaṃ ādiyantassa āpatti pārājikassa—"
msgstr "For one who steals there is an offense entailing expulsion when five factors are fulfilled:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:85.3"
msgid "paraparig­gahi­tañca hoti,"
msgstr "it is the possession of another;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:85.4"
msgid "paraparig­gahi­ta­saññī ca,"
msgstr "he perceives it as such;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:85.5"
msgid "garuko ca hoti parikkhāro, pañcamāsako vā ati­reka­pañca­māsako vā, theyyacittañca paccupaṭṭhitaṃ hoti."
msgstr "it is a valuable possession worth at least five <i lang=\"pli\">māsaka</i> coins;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:85.6"
msgid "theyyacittañca paccupaṭṭhitaṃ hoti."
msgstr "he has the intention to steal it;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:85.7"
msgid "Āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "if he touches it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct/"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:85.8"
msgid "Phandāpeti, āpatti thullaccayassa."
msgstr "if he makes it quiver, he commits a serious offense/"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:85.9"
msgid "Ṭhānā cāveti, āpatti pārājikassa."
msgstr "if he moves it from its base, he commits an offense entailing expulsion."

