msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:183.6"
msgid "Yo paribhuñjeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti."
msgstr "If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”"

#. </strong> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:183.7"
msgid "(143)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="178"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.2.7.44"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.368"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:184.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū uposathaggampi sannisajjampi harituṃ kukkuccāyantā chamāyaṃ nisīdanti."
msgstr "At that time, being afraid of wrongdoing, the monks did not take any equipment to the observance hall or to meetings, and they sat down on the bare ground."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:184.2"
msgid "Gattānipi cīvarānipi paṃsukitāni honti."
msgstr "Their limbs and robes became dusty."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:184.3"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "They informed the Master."

#. <strong class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:184.4"
msgid "“Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, tāvakālikaṃ haritun”ti."
msgstr "“I allow you to borrow."

#. </strong> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:184.5"
msgid "(144)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><hr><div class="bhikkhuni"><p><a class="sc" id="179"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.2.7.45"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.369"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:185.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena campāyaṃ thullanandāya bhikkhuniyā antevāsinī bhikkhunī thullanandāya bhikkhuniyā upaṭṭhākakulaṃ gantvā—"
msgstr "On one occasion at Campā, a nun who was a pupil of the nun Thullanandā went to a family who supported Thullanandā and said,"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.111"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:185.2"
msgid "“ayyā icchati tekaṭulayāguṃ pātun”ti,"
msgstr "“The Venerable wants to drink rice-porridge containing the three pungent ingredients.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:185.3"
msgid "pacāpetvā haritvā attanā paribhuñji."
msgstr "When it was ready, she took it away and ate it herself."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:185.4"
msgid "Sā jānitvā taṃ codesi—"
msgstr "When Thullananadā found out about this, she rebuked her, saying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:185.5"
msgid "“assamaṇīsi tvan”ti."
msgstr "“You’re no longer an ascetic.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:185.6"
msgid "Tassā kukkuccaṃ ahosi … pe …."
msgstr "She became remorseful …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:185.7"
msgid "Atha kho sā bhikkhunī bhikkhunīnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi."
msgstr "She then informed the nuns,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:185.8"
msgid "Bhikkhuniyo bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "who in turn informed the monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:185.9"
msgid "Bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "who then informed the Master."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:185.10"
msgid "“Anāpatti, bhikkhave, pārājikassa;"
msgstr "“There’s no offense entailing expulsion,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:185.11"
msgid "āpatti sam­pajā­na­musā­vāde pācittiyassā”ti."
msgstr "but there’s an offense entailing confession for lying.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:185.12"
msgid "(145)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="180"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.370"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:186.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena rājagahe thullanandāya bhikkhuniyā antevāsinī bhikkhunī thullanandāya bhikkhuniyā upaṭṭhākakulaṃ gantvā—"
msgstr "On one occasion in Rājagaha, a nun who was a pupil of the nun Thullanandā went to a family who supported Thullanandā and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:186.2"
msgid "“ayyā icchati madhugoḷakaṃ khāditun”ti,"
msgstr "“The Venerable wants to eat a honey-ball.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:186.3"
msgid "pacāpetvā haritvā attanā paribhuñji."
msgstr "When it was ready, she took it away and ate it herself."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:186.4"
msgid "Sā jānitvā taṃ codesi—"
msgstr "When Thullanandā found out about this, she rebuked her, saying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:186.5"
msgid "“assamaṇīsi tvan”ti."
msgstr "“You’re no longer an ascetic.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:186.6"
msgid "Tassā kukkuccaṃ ahosi … pe …"
msgstr "She became remorseful …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:186.7"
msgid "“anāpatti, bhikkhave, pārājikassa;"
msgstr "“There’s no offense entailing expulsion,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:186.8"
msgid "āpatti sam­pajā­na­musā­vāde pācittiyassā”ti."
msgstr "but there’s an offense entailing confession for lying.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:186.9"
msgid "(146)"
msgstr ""

#. </p></div><hr><p><a class="sc" id="181"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.2.7.46"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.371"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:187.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena vesāliyaṃ āyasmato ajjukassa upaṭṭhākassa gahapatino dve dārakā honti—"
msgstr "At one time in Vesāli, a householder who was a supporter of Venerable Ajjuka had two children living with him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:187.2"
msgid "putto ca bhāgineyyo ca."
msgstr "a son and a nephew."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:187.3"
msgid "Atha kho so gahapati āyasmantaṃ ajjukaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "That householder said to Ajjuka,"

#. VAR: saddho hoti pasanno tassa ācikkheyyāsī”ti → ācikkheyyāsīti so kālamakāsi (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:187.4"
msgid "“imaṃ, bhante, okāsaṃ yo imesaṃ dvinnaṃ dārakānaṃ saddho hoti pasanno tassa ācikkheyyāsī”ti."
msgstr "“Venerable, please assign this estate to the one of these two boys who has faith and confidence.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:187.5"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena tassa gahapatino bhāgineyyo saddho hoti pasanno."
msgstr "At that time the householder’s nephew had faith and confidence,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:187.6"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ajjuko taṃ okāsaṃ tassa dārakassa ācikkhi."
msgstr "and so Ajjuka assigned that estate to him."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.112"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:187.7"
msgid "So tena sāpateyyena kuṭumbañca saṇṭhapesi dānañca paṭṭhapesi."
msgstr "He then established a household with that wealth and made a gift."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:187.8"
msgid "Atha kho tassa gahapatino putto āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "The householder’s son then said to Venerable Ānanda,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:187.9"
msgid "“ko nu kho, bhante ānanda, pituno dāyajjo—"
msgstr "“Venerable Ānanda, who’s the father’s heir,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:187.10"
msgid "putto vā bhāgineyyo vā”ti?"
msgstr "the son or the nephew?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:187.11"
msgid "“Putto kho, āvuso, pituno dāyajjo”ti."
msgstr "“The son is the father’s heir.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:187.12"
msgid "“Ayaṃ, bhante, ayyo ajjuko amhākaṃ sāpateyyaṃ amhākaṃ methunakassa ācikkhī”ti."
msgstr "“Venerable, this Venerable Ajjuka has assigned our wealth to our housemate.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:187.13"
msgid "“Assamaṇo, āvuso, āyasmā ajjuko”ti."
msgstr "“Venerable Ajjuka is no longer an ascetic.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:187.14"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ajjuko āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "Ajjuka then said to Ānanda,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:187.15"
msgid "“dehi me, āvuso ānanda, vinicchayan”ti."
msgstr "“Ānanda, please investigate.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.67"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:187.16"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā upāli āyasmato ajjukassa pakkho hoti."
msgstr "On that occasion, Venerable Upāli was siding with Ajjuka,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:187.17"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā upāli āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and he said to Ānanda,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:187.18"
msgid "“yo nu kho, āvuso ānanda, sāmikena ‘imaṃ okāsaṃ itthannāmassa ācikkheyyāsī’ti vutto tassa ācikkhati, kiṃ so āpajjatī”ti?"
msgstr "“Ānanda, when one is asked by the owner to assign an estate to so-and-so, and one does so, what offense has one committed?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:187.19"
msgid "“Na, bhante, kiñci āpajjati, antamaso ­dukka­ṭa­mattampī”ti."
msgstr "“One hasn’t committed any offense, Venerable, not even one of wrong conduct.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:187.20"
msgid "“Ayaṃ, āvuso, āyasmā ajjuko sāmikena—‘imaṃ okāsaṃ itthannāmassa ācikkhā’ti vutto tassa ācikkhati;"
msgstr "“Venerable Ajjuka was asked by the owner to assign an estate to so-and-so, and he did so."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:187.21"
msgid "anāpatti, āvuso, āyasmato ajjukassā”ti."
msgstr "There’s no offense for Venerable Ajjuka.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:187.22"
msgid "(147)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="182"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.2.7.47"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.372"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:188.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bārāṇasiyaṃ āyasmato pilinda­vacchassa upaṭṭhākakulaṃ corehi upaddutaṃ hoti."
msgstr "At that time, in Benares, a family that supported Venerable Pilindavaccha was harassed by criminals,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:188.2"
msgid "Dve ca dārakā nītā honti."
msgstr "and two of their children were kidnapped."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:188.3"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā pilindavaccho te dārake iddhiyā ānetvā pāsāde ṭhapesi."
msgstr "Pilindavaccha brought the children back by his supernormal powers and placed them in a stilt house."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.113"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:188.4"
msgid "Manussā te dārake passitvā—"
msgstr "People saw those children and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:188.5"
msgid "“ayyassāyaṃ pilinda­vacchassa iddhānubhāvo”ti,"
msgstr "“This is the majesty of the supernormal powers of Venerable Pilindavaccha,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:188.6"
msgid "āyasmante pilindavacche abhippasīdiṃsu."
msgstr "and they placed confidence in him."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:188.7"
msgid "Bhikkhū ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "But the monks complained and criticized him:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:188.8"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma āyasmā pilindavaccho corehi nīte dārake ānessatī”ti."
msgstr "“How can Venerable Pilindavaccha bring back children who have been kidnapped by criminals?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:188.9"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "And they informed the Master."

#. <strong class="rule"> 
#. VAR: iddhimassa → iddhimato (bj) | iddhimantassa (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:188.10"
msgid "“Anāpatti, bhikkhave, iddhimassa iddhivisaye”ti."
msgstr "He said, “There’s no offense in the area of supernormal powers for one who possesses them.”"

#. </strong> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:188.11"
msgid "(148)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="183"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.2.7.48"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.373"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:189.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena dve bhikkhū sahāyakā honti—paṇḍuko ca kapilo ca."
msgstr "At one time, the two monks Paṇḍaka and Kapila were friends."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:189.2"
msgid "Eko gāmake viharati, eko kosambiyaṃ."
msgstr "One was staying in a village and one at Kosambī."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:189.3"
msgid "Atha kho tassa bhikkhuno gāmakā kosambiṃ gacchantassa antarāmagge nadiṃ tarantassa sūkarikānaṃ hatthato muttā medavaṭṭi pāde laggā hoti."
msgstr "Then, while the first monk was traveling from that village to Kosambī, he had to cross a river. As he did so, a lump of fat that had escaped from the hands of pork-butchers stuck to his foot."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:189.4"
msgid "So bhikkhu—“sāmikānaṃ dassāmī”ti aggahesi."
msgstr "He took hold of it, thinking, “I’ll give it to the owners.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:189.5"
msgid "Sāmikā taṃ bhikkhuṃ codesuṃ—"
msgstr "But the owners rebuked him, saying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:189.6"
msgid "“assamaṇosi tvan”ti."
msgstr "“You’re no longer an ascetic.”"

#. </p><p>
#. VAR: Taṃ uttiṇṇaṃ gopālikā → aññatarā gopālikā (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:189.7"
msgid "Taṃ uttiṇṇaṃ gopālikā passitvā etadavoca—"
msgstr "Then a woman cowherd who had seen him crossing said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:189.8"
msgid "“ehi, bhante, methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevā”ti."
msgstr "“Come, Venerable, have sexual intercourse.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:189.9"
msgid "So—“pakatiyāpāhaṃ assamaṇo”ti tassā methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevitvā"
msgstr "Thinking he was no longer an ascetic, he had sexual intercourse with her."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:189.10"
msgid "kosambiṃ gantvā bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi."
msgstr "When he arrived at Kosambī, he informed the monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:189.11"
msgid "Bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "and they in turn informed the Master."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:189.12"
msgid "“Anāpatti, bhikkhave, adinnādāne pārājikassa;"
msgstr "He said, “There’s no offense entailing expulsion for stealing,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:189.13"
msgid "āpatti methuna­dhamma­samā­yoge pārājikassā”ti."
msgstr "but there’s an offense entailing expulsion for having sexual intercourse.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:189.14"
msgid "(149)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="184"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.2.7.49"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.374"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.114"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:190.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena sāgalāyaṃ āyasmato daḷhikassa saddhivihāriko bhikkhu anabhiratiyā pīḷito āpaṇikassa veṭhanaṃ avaharitvā āyasmantaṃ daḷhikaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "At that time, at Sāgalā, a monk who was a student of Venerable Daḷhika was plagued by discontent. He then took a turban from a shopkeeper and said to Daḷhika,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:190.2"
msgid "“assamaṇo ahaṃ, bhante, vibbhamissāmī”ti."
msgstr "“Venerable, I’m no longer an ascetic; I’ll disrobe.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:190.3"
msgid "“Kiṃ tayā, āvuso, katan”ti?"
msgstr "“But what have you done?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:190.4"
msgid "So tamatthaṃ ārocesi."
msgstr "He told him."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:190.5"
msgid "Āharāpetvā agghāpesi."
msgstr "After getting the turban brought, Venerable Daḷhika had it valued,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:190.6"
msgid "Taṃ agghāpentaṃ na pañcamāsake agghati."
msgstr "and it was not worth five <i lang=\"pli\">māsaka</i> coins."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:190.7"
msgid "“Anāpatti, āvuso, pārājikassā”ti."
msgstr "“There’s no offense entailing expulsion,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:190.8"
msgid "Dhammakathaṃ akāsi."
msgstr "and he gave a teaching."

#. VAR: abhiramatīti → abhiramīti (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:190.9"
msgid "So bhikkhu abhiramatīti."
msgstr "That monk was delighted."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:190.10"
msgid "(150)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="185"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.375"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pj2:191.1"
msgid "Dutiya­pā­rāji­kaṃ samattaṃ."
msgstr "The second offense entailing expulsion is finished."

